abstract:
  pynxtools-raman is a reader plugin for pynxtools (https://github.com/FAIRmat-NFDI/pynxtools)
  written in Python. pynxtools-raman is a tool for reading and translating Raman spectroscopy
  data from proprietary and open data formats and standardizing it such that it is compliant with
  the NeXus application definitions NXoptical_spectroscopy and NXraman
  (https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nexus_definitions/).

  pynxtools-ellips is developed both as a standalone reader and as a tool within NOMAD, an open-source data
  management platform for materials science ((https://nomad-lab.eu/nomad-lab/).

  The work is funded by the Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (DFG, German Research Foundation) - 460197019 (FAIRmat)
  (https://gepris.dfg.de/gepris/projekt/460197019?language=en).
